ðŸ” Problem Restated (Simple Words)

Youâ€™re given an even-length array nums.

Your task:

Pair all numbers (each number used once)

Compute sum of each pair

Look at the maximum pair sum

Minimize that maximum value

Return that minimized maximum pair sum.

ðŸ§  Key Insight (Greedy Logic)

To minimize the maximum pair sum, you must balance pairs.

ðŸ‘‰ Pair smallest with largest, second smallest with second largest, and so on.

Why?

Pairing large numbers together creates a huge sum

Pairing large with small balances the load

This strategy keeps the maximum sum as low as possible

This is a classic Greedy + Two Pointers problem.

âœ… Optimal Approach: Sort + Two Pointers
ðŸš€ Approach Steps

Sort the array in ascending order

Use two pointers:

left â†’ start (smallest)

right â†’ end (largest)

Pair nums[left] + nums[right]

Track the maximum pair sum

Move pointers inward

Return the maximum found

âœï¸ Dry Run Example
Example 1

Input: [3,5,2,3]

Sorted â†’ [2,3,3,5]

Pair	Sum
2 + 5	7
3 + 3	6

ðŸ‘‰ Maximum = 7 âœ…

Example 2

Input: [3,5,4,2,4,6]

Sorted â†’ [2,3,4,4,5,6]

Pair	Sum
2 + 6	8
3 + 5	8
4 + 4	8

ðŸ‘‰ Maximum = 8 âœ…

ðŸ’¡ Why This Works (Greedy Proof)

Any other pairing creates larger imbalance

Small + Large pairing ensures:

Largest number is kept in check

No pair sum explodes unnecessarily

Hence, this strategy guarantees the minimum possible maximum sum

ðŸ§‘â€ðŸ’» JavaScript Code (Clean & Interview-Ready)
var minPairSum = function(nums) {
    // Step 1: Sort the array
    nums.sort((a, b) => a - b);

    let left = 0;
    let right = nums.length - 1;
    let maxPairSum = 0;

    // Step 2: Pair smallest with largest
    while (left < right) {
        let currentSum = nums[left] + nums[right];
        maxPairSum = Math.max(maxPairSum, currentSum);
        left++;
        right--;
    }

    return maxPairSum;
};

â±ï¸ Time & Space Complexity
ðŸ•’ Time Complexity

Sorting: O(n log n)

Two-pointer traversal: O(n)
âœ… Overall: O(n log n)

ðŸ§  Space Complexity

Sorting done in-place

Only variables used
âœ… O(1) (constant space)

ðŸ”¥ Interview Tip

If interviewer asks:

â€œWhy not pair largest together?â€

Answer:

Pairing largest together increases the maximum sum. Pairing smallest with largest balances each pair and guarantees the minimum possible maximum.

